<div class="content"><nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb"><a href="/">Home</a> › Vehicle Wrap Cost Chicago</nav><h1>How Much Do Vehicle Wraps Cost in Chicago?</h1><p class="lead speakable">Vehicle wrap costs in Chicago range from $400 for basic lettering to $10,000+ for large box truck full wraps. This guide breaks down pricing by vehicle type, coverage level, and fleet size — with transparent pricing from Chicago Fleet Wraps, Chicagoland's most experienced wrap shop with 9,400+ vehicles completed since 2001.</p><div class="cta-bar"><a href="/estimate/" class="btn btn-primary">Get an Instant Quote →</a><a href="tel:+13125971286" class="btn" style="border-color:var(--gold);color:var(--gold)">📞 Call for Pricing</a></div><div class="trust"><span>📅 <strong>24+ Years</strong> in Business</span><span>🏆 <strong>9,400+</strong> Vehicles Wrapped</span><span>✅ <strong>Avery Dennison & 3M</strong> Only</span><span>💰 <strong>Fleet Discounts</strong> up to 15%</span></div><div id="service-pain-bar" role="note" aria-label="Common fleet wrap pain points addressed" style="background:#0a0a0a;border-top:1px solid #222;border-bottom:1px solid #222;padding:28px 0;margin:0 -24px"><div style="max-width:960px;margin:0 auto;display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:0;border-left:3px solid #FFD700;padding:0 24px"><div style="padding:0 28px;border-right:1px solid #222"><p style="font-family:monospace;font-size:.62rem;letter-spacing:.12em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#FFD700;margin-bottom:6px">Branding</p><p style="font-size:.88rem;color:#ccc;line-height:1.6">Unwrapped vans miss 40,000+ daily impressions in the neighborhoods you already serve. Every unmarked panel is your competitor's free advertisement.</p></div><div style="padding:0 28px;border-right:1px solid #222"><p style="font-family:monospace;font-size:.62rem;letter-spacing:.12em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#FFD700;margin-bottom:6px">Durability</p><p style="font-size:.88rem;color:#ccc;line-height:1.6">Cheap calendered vinyl fails in 12–18 months in Chicago winters. We use only Avery Dennison MPI 1105 cast vinyl — rated 5–7 years, zero paint damage claims in 10+ years.</p></div><div style="padding:0 0 0 28px"><p style="font-family:monospace;font-size:.62rem;letter-spacing:.12em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#FFD700;margin-bottom:6px">Cost Efficiency</p><p style="font-size:.88rem;color:#ccc;line-height:1.6">Wraps are IRS Section 179 advertising expenses — 100% deductible year one. A $3,750 cargo van wrap costs ~$2,700 after tax at the 28% bracket. Fleet discounts up to 15%.</p></div></div></div><h2>Vehicle Wrap Pricing by Type</h2><table class="pricing-table"><tr><th>Vehicle Type</th><th>Full Wrap</th><th>Partial Wrap</th><th>Lettering</th></tr><tr><td>Sedan / Coupe</td><td>$2,500 – $4,000</td><td>$1,200 – $2,000</td><td>$400 – $800</td></tr><tr><td>SUV / Crossover</td><td>$3,000 – $5,000</td><td>$1,500 – $2,500</td><td>$500 – $900</td></tr><tr><td>Cargo Van (<a href="/van-wraps-chicago/" style="color:var(--gold)">details</a>)</td><td>$2,800 – $4,500</td><td>$1,400 – $2,200</td><td>$400 – $800</td></tr><tr><td>Sprinter Van (<a href="/sprinter/" style="color:var(--gold)">details</a>)</td><td>$3,500 – $5,200</td><td>$1,800 – $2,800</td><td>$500 – $1,000</td></tr><tr><td>Pickup Truck (<a href="/truck-wraps-chicago/" style="color:var(--gold)">details</a>)</td><td>$2,200 – $3,800</td><td>$1,200 – $2,000</td><td>$400 – $700</td></tr><tr><td>Box Truck 16–22 ft (<a href="/boxtruck/" style="color:var(--gold)">details</a>)</td><td>$4,200 – $7,500</td><td>$2,000 – $3,500</td><td>$600 – $1,200</td></tr><tr><td>Box Truck 24–26 ft</td><td>$7,000 – $10,000</td><td>$3,500 – $5,000</td><td>$800 – $1,500</td></tr></table><div class="pricing-cta-row" style="display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;padding:14px 20px;background:rgba(255,215,0,.04);border-left:3px solid #FFD700;border-bottom:1px solid #1e1e1e;gap:16px"><p style="font-family:monospace;font-size:.72rem;color:#888;letter-spacing:.06em">Free estimate response within 2 hours · Free fleet pickup included</p><a href="/estimate/?vehicle=cargo-van" style="display:inline-block;background:#FFD700;color:#000;font-family:monospace;font-size:.68rem;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:.1em;text-transform:uppercase;padding:10px 22px;text-decoration:none;white-space:nowrap;flex-shrink:0">Get My Cargo Van Estimate →</a></div><div class="pricing-cta-row" style="display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;padding:14px 20px;background:rgba(255,215,0,.04);border-left:3px solid #FFD700;border-bottom:1px solid #1e1e1e;gap:16px"><p style="font-family:monospace;font-size:.72rem;color:#888;letter-spacing:.06em">Sprinter vans from $3,500 · All lengths and roof heights</p><a href="/estimate/?vehicle=sprinter" style="display:inline-block;background:#FFD700;color:#000;font-family:monospace;font-size:.68rem;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:.1em;text-transform:uppercase;padding:10px 22px;text-decoration:none;white-space:nowrap;flex-shrink:0">Get My Sprinter Estimate →</a></div><div class="pricing-cta-row" style="display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;padding:14px 20px;background:rgba(255,215,0,.04);border-left:3px solid #FFD700;border-bottom:1px solid #1e1e1e;gap:16px"><p style="font-family:monospace;font-size:.72rem;color:#888;letter-spacing:.06em">Box trucks 16–26 ft · Full cab, sides, and rear coverage</p><a href="/estimate/?vehicle=box-truck" style="display:inline-block;background:#FFD700;color:#000;font-family:monospace;font-size:.68rem;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:.1em;text-transform:uppercase;padding:10px 22px;text-decoration:none;white-space:nowrap;flex-shrink:0">Get My Box Truck Estimate →</a></div><div class="pricing-cta-row" style="display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;padding:14px 20px;background:rgba(255,215,0,.04);border-left:3px solid #FFD700;border-bottom:1px solid #1e1e1e;gap:16px;margin-bottom:24px"><p style="font-family:monospace;font-size:.72rem;color:#888;letter-spacing:.06em">Pickup trucks from $2,200 · F-150, Silverado, Ram</p><a href="/estimate/?vehicle=pickup" style="display:inline-block;background:#FFD700;color:#000;font-family:monospace;font-size:.68rem;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:.1em;text-transform:uppercase;padding:10px 22px;text-decoration:none;white-space:nowrap;flex-shrink:0">Get My Pickup Estimate →</a></div><p class="body-text">All pricing includes <strong>design, print, professional installation, and UV-protective overlaminate</strong>. No hidden fees.</p><h2>What Affects Vehicle Wrap Cost?</h2><ul class="services"><li><strong>Vehicle Size</strong> — Larger vehicles require more material and labor. A 26-ft box truck uses 5x the vinyl of a sedan.</li><li><strong>Coverage Level</strong> — Full wraps cost more than partial wraps, which cost more than lettering. <a href="/partial-vehicle-wraps-chicago/" style="color:var(--gold)">Partial wrap details →</a></li><li><strong>Design Complexity</strong> — Simple logo placement vs. full custom illustration affects design time.</li><li><strong>Material Choice</strong> — Premium cast vinyl (what we use) costs more than calendered vinyl but lasts 3x longer.</li><li><strong>Fleet Size</strong> — Volume discounts reduce per-vehicle costs significantly.</li><li><strong>Special Finishes</strong> — Chrome, color-shift, and metallic films carry a premium over standard gloss/matte.</li></ul><h2>Fleet Discount Pricing</h2><table class="pricing-table"><tr><th>Fleet Size</th><th>Discount</th><th>Example Savings (Cargo Van)</th></tr><tr><td>3–4 Vehicles</td><td>5% off</td><td>Save $140–$225 per van</td></tr><tr><td>5–9 Vehicles</td><td>10% off</td><td>Save $280–$450 per van</td></tr><tr><td>10+ Vehicles</td><td>15% off</td><td>Save $420–$675 per van</td></tr></table><p class="body-text"><a href="/fleet-wraps-chicago/" style="color:var(--gold)">Learn more about our fleet wrap program →</a></p><h2>Full Wrap vs. Partial Wrap Pricing</h2><p class="body-text"><strong>Full wraps</strong> cover every visible panel for maximum brand impact. They generate the most impressions and deliver the best long-term ROI. Full wraps are the standard for <a href="/fleet-wraps-chicago/" style="color:var(--gold)">fleet branding programs</a>.</p><p class="body-text"><strong>Partial wraps</strong> cover strategic panels — typically sides, rear, and sometimes hood — at 40–60% of full wrap cost. They're ideal for businesses starting their fleet branding or working with tighter budgets. Most partial wraps deliver 60–80% of the visual impact of a full wrap.</p><h2>Wrap vs. Paint Cost Comparison</h2><table class="pricing-table"><tr><th>Option</th><th>Cost</th><th>Duration</th><th>Removable?</th></tr><tr><td>Professional Paint Job</td><td>$5,000 – $15,000+</td><td>Permanent</td><td>No — requires repainting</td></tr><tr><td>Premium Vinyl Wrap</td><td>$2,500 – $5,200</td><td>5–7 years</td><td>Yes — no paint damage</td></tr></table><p class="body-text">Vinyl wraps cost 50–75% less than professional paint, last 5–7 years, protect the factory paint, and can be changed whenever you rebrand. For businesses, wraps are also <strong>100% tax deductible</strong> under IRS Section 179 — paint is not.</p><h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2><div class="faq-item"><h3>How much does a vehicle wrap cost in Chicago?</h3><p>Vehicle wrap costs range from $1,200 for partial wraps to $10,000+ for large box trucks. Sedans: $2,500–$4,000. Cargo vans: $2,800–$4,500. Sprinter vans: $3,500–$5,200. Box trucks: $4,200–$10,000.</p></div><div class="faq-item"><h3>What factors determine the price of a vehicle wrap?</h3><p>Vehicle size, coverage level (full vs partial), design complexity, material choice, and fleet quantity all affect pricing. We use only premium cast vinyl — no cheap calendered material.</p></div><div class="faq-item"><h3>Is a vehicle wrap cheaper than paint?</h3><p>Yes. A professional paint job costs $5,000–$15,000+ and is permanent. A premium vinyl wrap costs $2,500–$5,200, lasts 5–7 years, protects the paint, and can be removed without damage.</p></div><div class="faq-item"><h3>Are vehicle wraps tax deductible?</h3><p>Yes — vehicle wraps used for business advertising are 100% tax deductible under IRS Section 179. The full cost can be deducted in the year of installation.</p></div></div>